      • generateInstance

        public static RedisAPI generateInstance(java.lang.String uri,
                                        java.lang.String password)
        Creates a new main Redis pool instance, there will only ever be one at a time so #getInstance should be used after generation
        Parameters:
        uri - the URI used to connect to the Redis server running
        password - the password used to connect to the Redis server running
        Returns:
        main instance of the api.RedisAPI
        Throws:
        CouldNotConnectToRedisException - signifies either an issue with the password passed through or the URI that is passed through the method

      • setFilterID

        public void setFilterID(java.lang.String filterId)
        This method is used to set a filter ID onto your Redis Pool, you can then use this when publishing messages to a channel to ensure that a specific RedisAPI instance receives your message
        Parameters:
        filterId - the filter id that you want to set your redis pool to

      • publishMessage

        public void publishMessage(java.lang.String filterId,
                           RedisChannel channel,
                           java.lang.String message)
        Publishes a message to the generated instances redis pool
        Parameters:
        filterId - the filter id for the message being sent, this filter id is checked by all the receiving pools to ensure that only a specific jedis pool handles the message
        channel - the channel object being published to, this is what should be registered on your other instances
        message - the message being sent across that channel

      • registerChannel

        public RedisChannel registerChannel(java.lang.String channelName,
                                    @NonNull
                                    @NonNull java.lang.Class<? extends RedisMessagingReceiveInterface> receiveEventClass)
        Used to register a redis channel, this must be done before sending any messages on this channel
        Parameters:
        channelName - the name of the channel, this is what is used when publishing a message
        receiveEventClass - the class which extends RedisMessagingReceiveInterface, this is where incoming messages on this channel will be sent
        Returns:
        object of the registered RedisChannel
        Throws:
        ChannelAlreadyRegisteredException - exception is thrown if channel with same name is already registered

      • registerChannel

        public RedisChannel registerChannel(java.lang.String channelName,
                                    @NonNull
                                    @NonNull java.util.function.Consumer<RedisMessagingReceiveEvent> receiveEventConsumer)
        Used to register a redis channel, this must be done before sending any messages on this channel
        Parameters:
        channelName - the name of the channel, this is what is used when publishing a message
        receiveEventConsumer - the consumer which has RedisMessagingReceiveEvent, this is where incoming messages on this channel will be sent
        Returns:

        Throws:
